How is this even a gun rights issue? The fight was over a craps game on what the article said was a """"predominantly Black college."""" Although the article does not come out and directly say it, the players were Black, got into a fist fight and then started bustin caps. Chances are extremely high that the gun used in the shooting was illegal anyway. So, how does all this make it a gun control issue? Are people actually that stupid to think that gun control laws would have actually kept the shooter from getting a gun? This is the 251st """"school shooting"""" since 1/1/15. In all cases, the schools were """"gun free zones."""" Can anyone identify a single instance since the advent of """"gun free zones"""" where they have worked in preventing a single shooting? How about any gun control law passed in the last 40 years?? The bottom line is the liberal way of thinking is getting people killed. Time for a change, folks.

The Republicans in congress started work on JFK's call for the civil rights act. LBJ, under pressure, asked congress to speed a bill a long, so some Democrats jumped on board to get a bill passed.
